dr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 To increase its appeal, Pivot is turning to names that would be familiar to millennials in realms like politics, Broadway, Hollywood and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (The channel specializes in purpose-driven programming because issues like protecting the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  appeal to many younger Americans, channel executives explain.)\par \par \uc2 For instance, Meghan McCain, who formerly hosted a show on Pivot called \u8220\'20\'1CRaising McCain,\u8221\'20\'1D will return to the channel. Ms. McCain, a daughter of Senator John McCain, will be one of three hosts of \u8220\'20\'1CTakePart Live,\u8221\'20\'1D a late-night talk show that the channel will move to 10 p.m. in May.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CTakePart Live\u8221\'20\'1D is also getting a new production company, Embassy Row, which specializes in live talk and chat shows like \u8220\'20\'1CWatch What Happens Live\u8221\'20\'1D on Bravo and \u8220\'20\'1CTalking Dead\u8221\'20\'1D on AMC.\par \par \uc2 The Broadway name joining the Pivot lineup is Lin-Manuel Miranda, the creator and star of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/10/theater/reviews/10heig.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the musical \u8220\'20\'1CIn the Heights,\u8221\'20\'1D}}}\uc2  who is working on {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/03/06/lin-manuel-mirandas-hamilton-heading-to-public-theater/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 a musical about Alexander Hamilton}}}\uc2 . Mr. Miranda, who also writes {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/06/12/about-that-tonys-rap/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the rap that Neil Patrick Harris delivered}}}\uc2  at the end of Tony Awards ceremonies, is among the cast members of \u8220\'20\'1CFreestyle Love Supreme,\u8221\'20\'1D an original show composed of 10 30-minute episodes that features performances of improvised, freestyle rhyme based on audience suggestions. \u8220\'20\'1CFreestyle Love Supreme,\u8221\'20\'1D billed by Pivot as a special, is scheduled to begin in October.\par \par \uc2 The Hollywood star power is to be supplied by the cast members of the channel\u8217\'20\'19s first original scripted series, \u8220\'20\'1CFortitude,\u8221\'20\'1D a 12-episode drama set in the Arctic. Pivot has given the show a green light in partnership with a unit of \uc2 British Sky Broadcasting\uc2 . {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sky.com/tv/show/fortitude/article/announcement"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The cast includes}}}\uc2  Stanley Tucci, Luke Treadaway, Michael Gambon and Christopher Eccleston.\par \par \uc2 In keeping with Pivot\u8217\'20\'19s tilt toward purpose programming, the drama is \u8220\'20\'1Can eco-thriller\u8221\'20\'1D that should appeal to Generation Y, \uc2 Evan Shapiro\uc2 , president of Pivot, said at a breakfast on Wednesday in Midtown Manhattan, where the channel held its 2014-15 upfront presentation.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Treadaway made brief remarks during the breakfast, as did Mr. Manuel and Ms. McCain. She drew laughs when she described how the \u8220\'20\'1Cnew election cycle\u8221\'20\'1D coming up in the fall \u8220\'20\'1Cis like Super Bowl time for me.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Also speaking at the breakfast was Tom Szaky, chief executive of a sustainability company, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.terracycle.com/en-US/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 TerraCycle}}}\uc2 , that will be the subject of an original, unscripted series called \u8220\'20\'1CHuman Resources.\u8221\'20\'1D Pivot plans 10 30-minute episodes of the show, starting on Aug. 8.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Shapiro called \u8220\'20\'1CHuman Resources\u8221\'20\'1D a \u8220\'20\'1Cdocu-comedy,\u8221\'20\'1D and that was borne out by the amusing clips he showed from the series, filmed at the TerraCycle office in New Jersey.\par \par \uc2 The channel\u8217\'20\'19s executives encourage advertisers to sign branded-entertainment deals in addition to running traditional commercials. Hyundai, Monster.com, Silk and Stonyfield are among brands that have worked with Pivot to create branded content like digital shorts, interstitial clips and 30-minute specials.\par \par \uc2 Pivot is available in about 45 million homes. The channel is not rated by Nielsen but intends to be, hence the expansion of its programming schedule \u8212\'20\'14 more than 300 hours of original shows in 2014, executives said \u8212\'20\'14 and its outreach to advertisers.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b ART\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Meghan McCain, center, with the other co-hosts of "TakePart Live," a talk show on the Pivot cable channel, Eddie Huang, left, and Jacob Soboroff, right. | Pivot | The Broadway star Lin-Manuel Miranda is among the cast members of a new original show on Pivot, "Freestyle Love Supreme." | Pivot   \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ppllus : \uc2 Participant 