n0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (Copyright (c) 2014, Dow Jones & Company, Inc.)   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 General Motors Co\uc2 . said on Tuesday it has no immediate plans to review how it manages safety standards further down its supply chain, three days after a deadly blast at a supplier's contractor in China.\par \par \uc2 The auto maker will continue the prevailing industry practice in which car makers rely on their direct component suppliers to monitor the safety standards of indirect suppliers further down the chain, the company's president said.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 "Our tier-one suppliers on a global basis are required to make sure that they are sourcing from suppliers that are implementing the right safety standards," GM President \uc2 Dan Ammann\uc2  said, referring to auto-component suppliers that deal directly with car makers. "We have uniform focus on safety from a company perspective all around the world." Mr. Ammann spoke at the opening of \uc2 GM\uc2 's International headquarters in Singapore.\par \par \uc2 On Saturday, an explosion in the eastern Chinese city of Kunshan killed at least 75 workers and injured 185 more at Kunshan Zhongrong Metal Production Co., a subcontractor to car-wheel-maker Citic Dicastal Wheel Manufacturing Co., which is a supplier to \uc2 GM\uc2 . Chinese authorities have faulted local officials for poor oversight of conditions at the plant.\par \par \uc2 The tragedy confronts \uc2 GM\uc2  with a challenge other big consumer products marketers with extensive Chinese supply chains have been dealing with for years: Lapses by little-known Chinese suppliers can quickly tarnish the reputation of a global brand.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Ammann said it is "too soon to tell" whether \uc2 GM\uc2  will change its approach to assuring that suppliers comply with good safety practices. Zhongrong "was a supplier to a supplier, as opposed to us, so we are a couple of steps removed," he said. "But obviously it is a tragic situation, regardless."\par \par \uc2 China Labor Watch, a U.S. watchdog group, on Monday challenged \uc2 GM\uc2 's effort to distance itself from Zhongrong, saying the auto maker "has a duty to ensure safe production in its supply chain, and it shares responsibility for this deadly explosion."\par \par \uc2 Electronics companies such as \uc2 Apple Inc\uc2 . and South Korea's \uc2 Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd\uc2 . "don't claim that second-tier suppliers are out of their range," said \uc2 Kevin Slaten\uc2 , a China Labor Watch program coordinator. "They've openly accepted that their entire supply chain is an integral part of their business."\par \par \uc2 Global auto makers have recently begun taking steps to better monitor the behavior of suppliers in developing markets.\par \par \uc2 In March, a group of 14 big auto and truck makers, including \uc2 General Motors\uc2 , \uc2 Ford Motor Co\uc2 ., \uc2 Fiat Chrysler Automobiles NV\uc2 , \uc2 Toyota Motor Corp\uc2 . and \uc2 Volkswagen AG\uc2 , agreed to a set of standards for their suppliers, governing working conditions, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , human rights and business ethics. The auto makers are working through the Automotive Industry Action Group of the U.S., and \uc2 CSR\uc2  Europe, a coalition of European corporations and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  groups.\par \par \uc2 As part of this effort, the AIAG is developing programs that auto makers or their direct suppliers can use to lead one-day training sessions to outline the expectations they have for suppliers on issues such as workplace safety, says Tanya Bolden, program manager for the AIAG.\par \par \uc2 The AIAG effort is similar to the programs developed by an electronics industry group, the Electronics Industry Citizenship Coalition, in response to criticism of the practices of Chinese subcontractors that supply \uc2 Apple\uc2  and other well-known consumer electronics brands, Ms. Bolden said. "We work with them [the EICC] on conflict minerals," she said.\par \par \uc2 Auto makers are relying on their large, direct suppliers to "cascade" training on safety and other workplace issues to their subcontractors, she said.\par \par \uc2 Jean-Michel Vallin, president of French auto-components giant \uc2 Faurecia\uc2 's China arm, said direct suppliers like \uc2 Faurecia\uc2  look out for product safety, as well as work conditions down the supply chain, on behalf of car makers. "It's pretty clear and well understood that it is part of our responsibility," he said.\par \par \uc2 Still, he says, the responsibility cannot be solely borne by auto-component suppliers. The authorities in each country need to develop and enforce proper health and safety regulations, he said, as well as the companies where accidents occur.\par \par \uc2 "Ultimately it's the responsibility of those managing the factory," Mr. Vallin said.\par \par \uc2 Incidents such as the Zhongrong explosion are one reason auto makers are investing more in efforts to see more clearly through the layers of their global supply chains.\par \par \uc2 "There's business value to being able to respond quickly" to an incident that could disrupt production or pose a threat to corporate reputation, says Jon Bovit, chief marketing officer of Resilinc, a Milpitas, Calif., company that maps supply chains for clients including \uc2 GM\uc2  and other auto makers.\par \par \uc2 In addition to concerns about safety, international pressure for global manufacturers to stop using so-called "conflict minerals," or raw materials mined in war zones or under human rights abuses, has driven companies to dig deeper than ever into their supply networks, Mr. Bovit says.\par \par \uc2 "We do get into the fourth and fifth tiers," he said.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=weco20140806000050"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gnmoc : \uc2 General Motors Company\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720