se.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 "My photographs try to highlight the so called 'oil curse.' The photographs show not only desperate areas like the Niger Delta, where the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the society are devastated by decades of oil spills, oil thefts, government negligence and corruption, but also daily life images where you can see the hard work that schools, NGOs and local individuals carry out in order to alleviate these imbalances for the betterment of the youth. Oil and gas rich countries like Luanda where you see young boys skateboarding, or in Ghana where a women washes her clothes, are all part of the same context where local NGOs operate to bring education and protection to vulnerable communities."\par \par \uc2 Sacco documented his understanding of how local and international organizations focus their energy on programs that aim to protect youths and women, by offering them education and social protection. Whynot association, for example, was founded in 2000 by a group of young people living in a slum to promote education and fight youth unemployment.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \