palpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2015. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 BRUSSELS \u8212\'20\'14 The {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/organizations/e/european_union/index.html?inline=nyt-org"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 European Union}}}\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s top trade official said on Tuesday that the bloc should continue studying a controversial provision in a proposed trade agreement with the United States, but stopped short of endorsing the measure.\par \par \uc2 At issue is a so-called investment guarantee, which would give companies the right to sue national governments to enforce the terms of any eventual trade deal. While American businesses and the United States government are pressing to include that provision, many Europeans oppose it. The measure has become one of the main sticking points in negotiations over the proposed trade pact, known as the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A review of more than 150,000 public comments on the matter \u8220\'20\'1Cclearly shows that there is a huge skepticism\u8221\'20\'1D toward the investment guarantee provision, Cecilia Malmstrom, the \uc2 European Union\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s trade commissioner, said in a statement on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 The trade pact itself is no sure bet, as negotiators on both sides of the Atlantic have shown little progress after more than a year of periodic talks. For European opponents of the investment guarantee provision, the concern is that if it became part of a trade agreement, it would give companies a legal opening to erode European standards in environmental protection, food quality and labor rights.\par \par \uc2 The issue has become the rallying point for groups that mistrust the \uc2 European Union\uc2 , which they see as being unable to control migration and trim unemployment in the bloc, and are suspicious of the United States, which is widely regarded as mismanaging its global power and clumsily imposing electronic surveillance that threatens the privacy of European citizens.\par \par \uc2 Powerful figures like Sigmar Gabriel, the German economy minister, have called that clause unnecessary, and Matthias Fekl, the French junior minister for trade, has said that including it would make any deal unacceptable to Europe.\par \par \uc2 But many American and European trade experts say the guarantee should be part of any modern trade agreement between the \uc2 European Union\uc2  and the United States, which have the two largest economies in the world. Such proponents note that recently agreed-upon European accords with Canada and Singapore contain the guarantee, although those pacts still await ratification by European lawmakers.\par \par \uc2 On Tuesday, Ms. Malmstrom said she was still not ready to recommend how to modify the guarantee or say whether it should be jettisoned. Instead she highlighted the main issues raised by the results of the 140-page {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://trade.ec.europa.eu/doclib/docs/2015/january/tradoc_153044.pdf"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 review of public comments}}}\uc2  and noted there were \u8220\'20\'1Careas that can be reformed.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 The proposed trade pact has been under formal negotiation since early 2013, when it was announced by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/o/barack_obama/index.html?inline=nyt-per"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 President Obama}}}\uc2  in his annual {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/subjects/s/state_of_the_union_message_us/index.html?inline=nyt-classifier"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 State of the Union address}}}\uc2 . It was initially welcomed by \uc2 European Union\uc2  leaders as a debt-free way to spur economic growth in a region plagued by a long {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/subjects/e/european_sovereign_debt_crisis/index.html?inline=nyt-classifier"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 debt crisis}}}\uc2  and high unemployment.\par \par \uc2 Yet {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/22/business/international/malmstrom-reinforces-plans-to-press-ahead-with-us-trade-talks.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 progress has been slow}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Despite seven rounds of rotating meetings in Washington and Brussels, the negotiators {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/06/13/business/global/to-create-jobs-europe-pushes-for-trade-deal-with-us.html?pagewanted=all"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 have been at odds}}}\uc2  over how to lower tariffs and, among other sticking points, whether to include financial services in any deal.\par \par \uc2 The next round of talks is scheduled in Brussels during the first week of February. But talks on the investment guarantee will remain suspended until the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/organizations/e/european_commission/index.html?inline=nyt-org"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 European Commission}}}\uc2 , the \uc2 European Union\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s executive branch, can try to hash out a possible compromise. Officials said on Tuesday that they had no firm timetable for taking that step.\par \par \uc2 The call for comments on the investment guarantee was conducted by the \uc2 European Commission\uc2  from March through July, and generated 150,000 responses. \uc2 European Union\uc2  officials said that was probably a record for such an exercise, although it indicated there might have been considerable lobbying by advocacy groups, as about 145,000 of those responses were submitted through online platforms using \u8220\'20\'1Cpredefined, negative answers.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 The comments \u8212\'20\'14 officially known as a public consultation \u8212\'20\'14 showed trade unions and other campaign groups seeking more assurances that governments could regulate in the public interest, and seeking obligations on businesses to abide by standards on human rights, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to the commission.\par \par \uc2 But \u8220\'20\'1Cexcluding investment protection from the T.T.I.P. negotiations is simply not an option,\u8221\'20\'1D said Lourdes Catrain, a partner in Brussels with the law firm \uc2 Hogan Lovells\uc2 , using the trade proposal\u8217\'20\'19s acronym.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe United States is the E.U.\u8217\'20\'19s largest trading partner, and it clearly wants investment protection," said Ms. Catrain, whose firm advised companies participating in the public consultation. \u8220\'20\'1CLeaving it out of that deal would weaken Europe\u8217\'20\'19s negotiating position with China and other parts of the world where European companies are seeking similar investment protections.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b ART\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The European Union's top trade official,\u160\'00\'A0Cecilia Malmstrom, said review of public comments shows \u8220\'20\'1Chuge skepticism\u8221\'20\'1D toward an investment guarantee provision in a proposed trade pact with the United States. | Julien Warnand/European Pressphoto Agency   \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 euruno : \uc2 The European Union | usagov : \uc2 United States Federal Government\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clp