lt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Part of the reason for the shift is that companies have recognised that they can be more useful to community organisations if they offer skills and services, which can also be more valuable than cash donations.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWe look at how to create value through the assets we have as a company \u8212\'20\'14 both our people and the professionals skills we have and our products in terms of solutions that leverage data, software and services,\u8221\'20\'1D says Celia Moore, \uc2 IBM\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s London-based director of corporate citizenship. \u8220\'20\'1CAnd the same services we take to our clients are relevant to support other parts of the community.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 When it comes to deploying their employees as volunteers, a more strategic approach prevails, too. After all, while it might be fun for employees to spend a day painting a school, if they are lawyers or IT consultants, their time could be spent much more productively.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, if they are harnessing the expertise and knowledge they use in the workplace to tackle social problems, they are more likely to pick up additional skills from working in a context that can be very different from a corporate \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIt\u8217\'20\'19s not about a one-way transfer of wisdom,\u8221\'20\'1D says Paul Woodgates, an education expert and head of the Teach First initiative at \uc2 PA Consulting Group\uc2 . \u8220\'20\'1CIt\u8217\'20\'19s much more mutual than that.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 For some, the more strategic approach to community engagement has been driven by a desire to bring a stronger focus to their social investments, making them more likely to become permanent programmes rather than one-off initiatives.\par \par \uc2 This was the thinking behind \uc2 PA Consulting Group\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s partnership with Teach First. \u8220\'20\'1CAbout a year ago, we took a decision to focus our charitable efforts,\u8221\'20\'1D says Mr Woodgates. \u8220\'20\'1CWe were doing small amounts of time for a large number of causes and we thought there would be greater value in doing a smaller number of things but with more time and effort.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the concept of \u8220\'20\'1Ccommunity\u8221\'20\'1D has expanded. This might lead companies to contribute to anything from food relief efforts in crisis-hit regions to healthcare services in developing countries.\par \par \uc2 In the BITC Responsible Business Awards, for example, the International Disaster Relief Award recognises companies such as GSK and Zurich (see case studies) that are using their skills and expertise, products and services to contribute to relief efforts.\par \par \uc2 British Airways\uc2 , another of the finalists in this category, works with partners to help deliver supplies to communities hit by disaster, including flying in specialists that can provide mental, social and emotional support.\par \par \uc2 As companies have become global organisations, so have their community investment initiatives. This may mean adapting programmes to suit different cultures and local conditions.\par \par \uc2 To do so, \uc2 IBM\uc2  works with organisations that are experienced in volunteering in different parts of the world, such as VSO and Australian Business Volunteers.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWe also work with our business in the country to understand the need and to look at what organisations they know,\u8221\'20\'1D says \uc2 IBM\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s Ms Moore. \u8220\'20\'1CSo it\u8217\'20\'19s very much a collaboration between expert NGOs and bringing our own business knowledge to identify organisations.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 And, as at home, in developing countries, companies also can harness what they do best to support local communities. In Senegal, for example, Orange, the French telecoms company, recently launched its second D4D (Data for Development) challenge, making anonymous data from the mobile network available to international research laboratories to advance socio-economic development.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWe\u8217\'20\'19re putting technology at the service of society,\u8221\'20\'1D says Brigitte Dumont director of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  at Orange. \u8220\'20\'1CAnd digital technology could be a catalyst for progress.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 pamanc : \uc2 PA Consulting Group\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 icnsl : \uc2 Business Consultancy | iacc : \uc2 Accounting/Consulting | ibcs : \uc2 Business/Consumer Services | i83951 : \uc2 Management Consulting\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctl