crisis, the world track and field championships that ended in Beijing on Sunday provided some unexpected relief.\par \par \uc2 That may prove as temporary as last week\u8217\'20\'19s blue skies over Beijing \u8212\'20\'14 a result of restrictions on commuting and industry that were put in place by the Chinese authorities in advance of the upcoming major military parade.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 But track and field and its leadership will take fair weather wherever they can find it in these days of doping doom and the ever-longer shadow cast by soccer, the planet\u8217\'20\'19s No. 1 sport.\par \par \uc2 Over the past half-century, track and field has gone from mainstream to niche in countries like the United States and lost momentum in strongholds like Europe. Reversing such trends is as tough a task as outkicking Mo Farah on a bell lap, but the nine days in Beijing were a reminder of the entertainment value that track and field still can provide.\par \par \uc2 There were great races galore: From the men\u8217\'20\'19s 100 meters, where Usain Bolt beat Justin Gatlin by just one-hundredth of a second, to both 4x400 relays, where the Jamaican women and American men prevailed after final-leg lead changes.\par \par \uc2 There were overwhelming victories: Ashton Eaton\u8217\'20\'19s latest world record in the decathlon. There were triumphs of the human spirit: Aries Merritt\u8217\'20\'19s bronze medal in the men\u8217\'20\'19s 110 hurdles just four days before he was to receive a kidney transplant.\par \par \uc2 There was also some levity, provided by the Chinese driver of the Segway who crashed Bolt\u8217\'20\'19s victory celebration after the 200 meters, veering out of control and clipping the track star from behind. It could have been disastrous had Bolt come up lame. Instead, it was slapstick, not to mention irresistible content for the new media that the sport\u8217\'20\'19s recently crowned leader, Sebastian Coe, is so eager to leverage.\par \par \uc2 But the cameraman\u8217\'20\'19s gaffe was the exception to the rule for the Chinese organizers, who put on a smooth-running show in their underutilized showplace, the Bird\u8217\'20\'19s Nest stadium, which will take its next star turn as the site of the opening and closing ceremonies for the 2022 Winter Olympics.\par \par \uc2 The last two world championships in Daegu, South Korea, in 2011 and Moscow in 2013 suffered from mediocre attendance. Beijing had buzz and impressive crowds from the start: 34,000 on average in day sessions and 43,000 in the evening.\par \par \uc2 Liu Xiang, the Olympic 110 hurdles champion in 2004 who is now retired, became a celebrity in China in part because he succeeded in an event traditionally dominated by Western nations. There was similar frisson here when the Chinese sprinter Su Bingtian became the first Asian to qualify for the men\u8217\'20\'19s 100 final; reinforced when Su and his teammates ended up with a silver medal in the 4x100 relay.\par \par \uc2 Several of the young Chinese athletes, including the silver medalist high jumper Zhang Guowei, have big personalities and no qualms about communicating their emotions to the crowd. For all of track and field\u8217\'20\'19s obstacles in its traditional markets, generating greater interest in China, the world\u8217\'20\'19s most populous nation, could make up for a lot of ills.\par \par \uc2 Coe, a Briton who was once the world\u8217\'20\'19s best middle-distance runner, took over as president of the International Association of Athletics Federations on Monday. Change at the top was overdue: Outgoing president Lamine Diack is 82.\par \par \uc2 \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18It was getting stagnant,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 said Christian Taylor, the American triple jumper who won gold in Beijing.\par \par \uc2 Coe is 58, and as a former top athlete he has deep connections throughout the sport. A gifted speaker, he should also be able to communicate more widely and effectively than the French-speaking Diack, who struggled with English and, in his final news conference, with clarity, as he rambled on about the eternal elephant in track and field\u8217\'20\'19s room: doping.\par \par \uc2 Diack\u8217\'20\'19s final point was essentially that track and field has been a pioneer in anti-doping efforts, not a laggard. There is truth in this, but the scandals and suspicions keep coming. Coe, who once pushed for life bans for major doping violations, understands the landscape better than most. Even his own breakthrough performances in the 1970s forced him to answer some questions.\par \par \uc2 \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18A kid comes out of a municipal \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Sheffield and suddenly runs 1:42.4 and it\u8217\'20\'19s the overnight wonder,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 Coe said. \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18They tend to forget of course that the overnight wonder is the creation of thousands of miles on moorland and tons of steel in the gym.\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18What we need to get across is there has to be some proportionality in this. Our sport is not a monologue of blood and urine,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 he said. \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18It is Jesse Owens and Emil Zatopek and Fanny Blankers-Koen.\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 Coe already has talked about outsourcing some testing to an entity independent of the I.A.A.F. In an interview in Beijing, he said he intended to start a new committee focused on values and on reaching athletes at an early stage in their careers to educate them about the sport\u8217\'20\'19s history and better prepare them to combat ethical dilemmas.\par \par \uc2 \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18I would love to know what was going on in the lives and influences of some of our athletes from the age of 17 or 18 onwards,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 Coe said. \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18What was going on in Lance Armstrong\u8217\'20\'19s life or in Justin Gatlin\u8217\'20\'19s life? I think we can\u8217\'20\'19t be oblivious to that.\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 On the topic of his own potential ethical dilemmas, Coe rejected the notion that he should be obliged to abandon his role as a paid consultant to \uc2 Nike\uc2  or his executive chairman\u8217\'20\'19s role with the marketing agency CSM.\par \par \uc2 \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18My legal counsel,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 Coe said, \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18and she\u8217\'20\'19s the best in class and has been with me for many years, has always quite rightly said conflict exists if it\u8217\'20\'19s not registered. Conflict exists if you can\u8217\'20\'19t stand behind process and procedure and a conflict exists if you behave badly. And I don\u8217\'20\'19t intend to do any of those three.\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 The I.A.A.F. presidency is an unpaid post. Coe thinks it should remain so but said he wanted to maintain his outside income and above all was convinced that he could manage his multiple roles with great transparency and strict adherence to corporate governance rules. He said he navigated these waters in his years in \uc2 British Parliament\uc2  and his years as head of the organizing committee for the 2012 London Olympics, when, as he points out, \uc2 Nike\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s rival Adidas was a primary sponsor. He has said his role with \uc2 Nike\uc2  does not involve negotiating contracts but involves a \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  project designed to fight child obesity.\par \par \uc2 \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18I did not take this on to make money,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 he said of the I.A.A.F. presidency. \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18Or to advance my outside interests. These will be ferociously policed. Believe me.\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 But even with effective policing, minding the gap between perception and reality could still prove a problem. \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18He is definitely the man for the job,\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19 said Mary Wittenberg, the former chief of the New York City Marathon. \u8216\'20\'18\u8216\'20\'18It\u8217\'20\'19s really important that he seizes the moment to lead, to step above all potential conflict. Ditch the \uc2 Nike\uc2  and any other consulting arrangements.\u8217\'20\'19\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 At a moment of such clear importance for his sport, the last thing Coe and track and field need is for his own message to get clouded.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gathl : \uc2 Athletics | gdop : \uc2 Doping/Drug Tests | gspo : \uc2 Sports/Recreation | ncolu : \uc2 Columns | gabus : \uc2 Drug/Substance Usage | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gcom : \uc2 Society/Community | ghea : \uc2 Health | gmed : \uc2 Medical Conditions | gsoc : \uc2 Social Issues | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfce : \uc2 C&E Exclusion Filter | nrgn : \uc2 Routine General News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnu