ight\rin0\lin0 \uc2 WSJO\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2015 Dow Jones & Company, Inc. All Rights Reserved.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Paying attention to environmental and other social-responsibility issues might make a company more attractive to shareholders and customers. But does it matter to bondholders?\par \par \uc2 In other words, will at least some investors accept a lower yield on bonds because they believe the issuing company is socially responsible\u8212\'20\'14and expect a higher yield from companies they view as less responsible?\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The answer is yes, researchers say in a paper published in June in the Journal of Accounting and Public Policy, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0278425415000496"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1C\\b Corporate Social Responsibility\\b0  and the Cost of Corporate Bonds."}}}\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1COur results indicate that firms with better CSR [\b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 ] performance are able to issue bonds at lower cost and that both CSR strengths and concerns are considered by bondholders," wrote the authors, Mingzhi Liu and Wenxia Ge, professors at the University of Manitoba Asper School of Business in Winnipeg, Manitoba. The study also found a correlation between social responsibility and bonds' credit ratings.\par \par \uc2 Broad concerns\par \par \uc2 Bondholders are concerned about a range of social-responsibility issues, the study found, though not necessarily out of the goodness of their hearts. Social responsibility might offer several clues to a company's financial stability and prospects, suggests Dr. Liu, an assistant professor of accounting and finance at Asper.\par \par \uc2 The researchers found a link between bond yield spreads\u8212\'20\'14a measure of companies' borrowing costs\u8212\'20\'14and companies' scores on seven types of social-responsibility measures, including community involvement, corporate governance, employee relations, and product features such as quality, safety and social impact.\par \par \uc2 The effect is stronger for certain types of corporations. For instance, social-responsibility scores and bond yield spreads are more closely associated, statistically, for companies with stronger financial statements and for those in industries where the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  is an issue, as well as companies issuing investment-grade bonds, the researchers found.\par \par \uc2 Looking for signs\par \par \uc2 Dr. Liu points out one reason bondholders might favor companies with high CSR scores: Those companies may be less likely to be targets of costly and potentially crippling lawsuits that could lower the value of their bonds. \u8220\'20\'1CCSR-related information captures the dimension of a corporation's environmental risk" and the related litigation risk, he says.\par \par \uc2 He adds that high scores on various social-responsibility categories could also mean that management is looking after the company's reputation, a concern for any investor. And because environmental or other socially responsible projects can be expensive, embarking on such campaigns could be taken as a sign of a company's financial strength, Dr. Liu says.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CNormally, only financially healthy firms have enough cash flows to support CSR activities continuously," he says, so investors \u8220\'20\'1Ccould judge corporate CSR investment as a positive signal" in that regard.\par \par \uc2 Ms. Schoenberger is a writer in New York. She can be reached at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:reports@wsj.com"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 reports@wsj.com}}}\uc2 .\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\a