spnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2015 The Financial Times Ltd. All rights reserved. Please do not cut and paste FT articles and redistribute by email or post to the web.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The recent \u8216\'20\'18incident\u8217\'20\'19 with \uc2 Volkswagen\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s software manipulation has helped to shed light on the reputational risk issues companies face when it comes to their ethical, social and governance decisions.\par \par \uc2 This topic has been heavily debated throughout our MBA programme. Why? Because the social responsibility agenda is high on the modern-day consumer\u8217\'20\'19s radar, driving home the reality that companies cannot hide from the ever-increasingly \u8216\'20\'18conscious\u8217\'20\'19 investor.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The concept of responsible leadership is deeply integrated into the \uc2 University of Edinburgh\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s MBA programme. Through coursework, debates and guest lectures, we\u8217\'20\'19ve been constantly evaluating the way companies are making decisions (or failing to) with regard to their \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  and sustainability goals.\par \par \uc2 This week we heard from Fionna Ross, a senior analyst with \uc2 Aberdeen Asset Management\uc2  (\uc2 AAM\uc2 ). \uc2 AAM\uc2  is a global investment management group, managing assets for both institutional and retail clients. The group\u8217\'20\'19s mission is \u8220\'20\'1Cto deliver strong fund performance across diverse asset classes in which we believe we have a sustainable competitive edge\u8221\'20\'1D.\par \par \uc2 So what is \u8216\'20\'18a sustainable competitive edge\u8217\'20\'19? Well, Fionna\u8217\'20\'19s role, as part of the Responsible Investment team based locally here in Edinburgh, is to evaluate the social, environmental, and governance risk management of companies that \uc2 AAM\uc2  holds positions in, and use this information to ultimately to decide whether or not to invest in these businesses. This is known as \u8216\'20\'18ESG integration\u8217\'20\'19.\par \par \uc2 AAM\uc2  offers several types of responsible investing products for its clients. The first of these are SRI (socially responsible investing) products, which take a negative screening approach.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CEssentially, we screen out companies that fail on ethical measures,\u8221\'20\'1D Fionna says.\par \par \uc2 Sometimes, she says, it means steering away from investing in certain businesses or sectors \u8211\'20\'13 for example, companies operating within the nuclear, tobacco, weapons, gambling, pornography, alcohol, or military industries can be omitted, depending on particular factors. These factors can include the companies\u8217\'20\'19 performance and approach towards their \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , labour, human rights and business practices, and product quality.\par \par \uc2 So does this mean avoiding these investments altogether? Not necessarily, Fionna says.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIf we decided to divest in these companies or sectors entirely, then how would anyone influence them to improve?\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 A major strategy of \uc2 AAM\uc2  is therefore centred around engagement, where establishing long-term relationships helps to build trust and ultimately influence on performance on ESG factors.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWe are all about face-to-face visits with the companies we invest in \u8211\'20\'13 we have to understand the culture of these companies. That\u8217\'20\'19s a really big one for us,\u8221\'20\'1D Fionna says.\par \par \uc2 Increasingly, ESG considerations are being taken into account for not just SRI products, but also for unconstrained funds. Fionna explained that \u8220\'20\'1CCorporate governance (the \u8216\'20\'18G\u8217\'20\'19 of \u8216\'20\'18ESG\u8217\'20\'19) has always been an important part of the initial investment assessment stage, but we\u8217\'20\'19re looking to further integrate \u8216\'20\'18E\u8217\'20\'19 and \u8216\'20\'18S\u8217\'20\'19 considerations into the decision making process.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIts all about holistic risk management which is our assessment of all aspects that could pose a risk to the business \u8211\'20\'13 financially and through ESG factors \u8211\'20\'13 and we do this through a gap analysis. We try to turn risks into opportunities. One way of doing this is to link risk assessment and performance to employee, senior management and board remuneration.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 So is this the new normal? Arguably, yes. Shareholder value is highly correlated to sustainable decision-making and leadership \u8211\'20\'13 just take a look at the \uc2 Volkswagen\uc2  share price today. Here we have a clear reflection of how poor environmental and social decisions made at a senior level of the business have negatively impacted its bottom line. And not just for a week or two \u8211\'20\'13 the wider implications of this scandal are likely to have long-lasting effects on the business and the motor vehicle industry more broadly.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CCollectively investors can have that sort of impact,\u8221\'20\'1D Fionna says.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CInvestors are setting the agenda on ethical practices and how certain information is published by companies. ESG is not static, its an evolving space.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 I am inclined to agree. Sustainability and the reporting of companies\u8217\'20\'19 performance around ESG factors will continue to become more integrated into the investment landscape. However, in the ever-watchful eyes of the investor, the way businesses transform their \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  agendas into more than just lip service will be the \u8216\'20\'18make or break\u8217\'20\'19 measure of success.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 iresinv : \uc2 Sustainable Investment | i81502 : \uc2 Trusts/Funds/Financial Vehicles | ialtinv : \uc2 Alternative Investments | ifinal : \uc2 Financial Services | iinv : \uc2 Investing/Securities\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha