om article last month about the goings-ons at the historic climate change conference in Paris when my eyes stumbled across what appeared to be a fish-out-of-water participant - the \uc2 NHL\uc2 . The piece mentioned that an NHL vice president for \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Omar Mitchell, presented on sports and sustainability. I had to call the league.\par \par \uc2 Here's an excerpt from my conversation with Mitchell about the league's position.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Q: What was a vice president of the National Hockey League doing in Paris speaking at a forum tangentially connected to the historic U.N. climate change summit?\par \par \uc2 A: Our game, which is probably unique to most other professional sports, is so tied to the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We need cold weather; we need fresh water in order to play. Therefore, our game is directly impacted by climate change and fresh water scarcity. So we developed \uc2 NHL\uc2  Green, a mandate to promote this type of awareness across all of our organizations. . . .\par \par \uc2 There's a movement in the sports world that's really prioritizing sustainability around premier events like the Olympics, like FIFA World Cup, like the Super Bowl and organizations like ours that are really putting this at the forefront. . . . Green Sports Alliance, which is a nonprofit organization based in the U.S., has been a catalyst for this movement. Green Sports Alliance is also our principal environmental adviser. They participated in this panel that was called Sustainability, Innovation and Sport. They invited people who are really championing these initiatives to come and speak so that we could share those best practices. So we were very fortunate to be offered an invite to come and speak, and that's why we were there.\par \par \uc2 Q: What involvement is there of individual owners, coaches or players in this effort?\par \par \uc2 A lot of the players are interested. One that comes to mind immediately is Andrew Ference. He's a self-proclaimed eco-athlete. He really prioritizes this in his life. So he's a big environmental champion.\par \par \uc2 Our next stage is to engage more players around this issue because when we put out stuff on our social media platforms, 12 million followers on social media, that definitely gets messaging out to fans. . . . We need to educate our athletes on this issue because they grew up on frozen ponds. They get the connection between learning to play outside and environmental issues. They get it.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CT\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 http://www.washingtonpost.com\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li