ng.   All Rights Reserved.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 After a relatively somber 2015, it looks like humor will be back in full force during Super Bowl 50.\par \par \uc2 From Seth Rogen and Amy Schumer hosting a Bud Light party to the possibility of Steve Harvey spoofing his Miss Universe mix-up, there's likely to be a lot more levity in the commercials that air when the big game is played Feb. 7. That comes after a year in which one of the most talked-about spots was a Nationwide ad centered around a child who'd died.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 "I don't think there's any doubt there's going to be a return to humor," says Charles Taylor, a marketing professor at Villanova University who also edits the International Journal of Advertising. "And I do think it's partially a reaction to last year's game having more ads with a very serious tone."\par \par \uc2 Shock Top, an \uc2 Anheuser-Busch\uc2  wheat beer that's a newcomer to the Super Bowl, will feature a wise-cracking orange wedge trading barbs with comic T.J. Miller. Christopher Walken's quirky persona will be on full display in a 60-second Kia ad for the carmaker's new 2016 Optima midsize sedan. And Mountain Dew, along with Skittles, whose Super Bowl ad will feature rocker Steven Tyler, may also make a play for the funny bone, Taylor says.\par \par \uc2 But that's not the only trend emerging as advertisers roll out sneak peeks at their marketing campaigns. While it may be less common than last year, some brands are still expected to use their moment on one of the biggest marketing stages in sports, to drive home messages of social responsibility.\par \par \uc2 Colgate\uc2 , for instance, in its Super Bowl debut will champion water conservation.\par \par \uc2 "A big part of this is, in a really competitive \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , companies need to think about \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Taylor says.\par \par \uc2 Taylor pointed to last year's \uc2 Microsoft\uc2  ads in the Super Bowl, which put the spotlight on a woman who connects children to technology on her computer-filled bus. They showed how the company's technology helped Braylon O'Neill, a boy with prosthetic legs. He says they are examples of how such messages can resonate positively.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the ad from Nationwide, the big insurer, remains controversial. A boy talks about all the milestones in life he missed, like riding a bike, because he died before he could achieve them. Then, an overflowing bathtub is shown.\par \par \uc2 "That's really the ad more people were talking about last year than any other," Taylor says. "I think Nationwide's intentions were very good in calling attention to accidents involving children in the home. People just didn't want to think about a child dying while they were watching the Super Bowl."\par \par \uc2 The use of social media platforms to help build brand buzz has also been accelerating, from mid-game tweets, to mobile-based contests. This year, Taylor says, look for the real-time airing of ads on \uc2 YouTube\uc2  that are pegged to a particular moment in the game.\par \par \uc2 "This has the potential of being the biggest thing to come out of this year's Super Bowl," he says. "I think it's a brilliant way of dealing with these multitasking and multimedia younger consumers."\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b ART\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 photo     Colgate   \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c32 : \uc2 Advertising | c31 : \uc2 Marketing/Markets | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpin : \uc2 C&E Industry News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\