i0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b ET\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 06:23 PM GMT\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b SN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Financial Times (FT.Com)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b SC\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 FTCOM\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2016 The Financial Times Ltd. All rights reserved. Please do not cut and paste FT articles and redistribute by email or post to the web.   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The way companies approach philanthropy is changing. Over the course of my MBA, I have had first-hand insights into the transformation taking place across the \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  (CSR) landscape.\par \par \uc2 CSR programmes have been a function of many businesses for years. Traditionally, they have existed as a way for organisations to \u8220\'20\'1Cgive back\u8221\'20\'1D funds or in-kind support to a chosen charity, not-for-profit or non-governmental organisation.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 No one would argue against the merits of CSR and charity support. However, the way in which companies are engaging in CSR these days is evolving. We\u8217\'20\'19ve been exploring this evolution throughout our business ethics coursework. Primarily, this has involved a consulting project with \uc2 Johnson & Johnson\uc2  the pharmaceuticals and healthcare company.\par \par \uc2 We\u8217\'20\'19ve been examining the business case for \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  \u8211\'20\'13 exploring ways in which companies can actually extract value and tangible benefits through their CSR programmes, so there is a mutual, long-term benefit to the partners involved. This is a concept known as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://hbr.org/2011/01/the-big-idea-creating-shared-value"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1Cshared value\u8221\'20\'1D}}}\uc2 , initially developed by Michael Porter, a professor at Harvard Business School and Mark Kramer, a professor at Harvard\u8217\'20\'19s Kennedy School of Government.\par \par \uc2 What\u8217\'20\'19s becoming more apparent is the way effectively-run CSR programmes can bring about tangible benefits that flow both ways. It is no longer about a one-off donation or transaction made by a corporate to a charity partner. A successful and meaningful CSR programme now involves more engagement between the corporate and the partner, built by relationships and a shared understanding of each other\u8217\'20\'19s needs and values.\par \par \uc2 Johnson & Johnson\uc2  is a company with strong CSR-based values, expressed through the business\u8217\'20\'19s {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.jnj.com/about-jnj/jnj-credo"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Credo}}}\uc2 , helping to guide its employees, management, stakeholders and even shareholders, towards the goals and values of the company.\par \par \uc2 Ian Walker, corporate citizenship director at J&J, helped shed light on effective CSR through initiatives taking place under his leadership.\par \par \uc2 Mr Walker says that of course it is important to look after the financials, but it is equally important how you go about it and how you act sustainably.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CAnyone can make a quick buck, but if you do it ethically, you\u8217\'20\'19ll be able to do it long term. How do your actions benefit society? You can throw money around and it can make a big difference through relief and short-term projects. But, these are short-term. Companies do this all the time but it\u8217\'20\'19s not sustainable.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Mr Walker puts it simply:\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIf you give someone a fish \u8211\'20\'13 that\u8217\'20\'19s charity, but teach them how to fish \u8211\'20\'13 that\u8217\'20\'19s sustainability\u8221\'20\'1D.\par \par \uc2 After various consultations and site visits with J&J and \uc2 Ethicon\uc2  (J&J\u8217\'20\'19s medical equipment arm) our cohort of MBAs presented on various benefits and opportunities that lie in effective CSR programmes in the context of J&J and the work the business does with organisations such as the Tropical Health and Education Trust.\par \par \uc2 My takeaways are:\par \par \uc2 * CSR is not about a one-off, one-way donation. It is an opportunity for business leaders and their companies to go one step further to innovate and also find a competitive advantage.\par \par \uc2 * Successful CSR is more about strategic investment than philanthropy. This is achieved through creating shared value via strategic partnerships that have the power to achieve long-lasting impacts for multiple stakeholders.\par \par \uc2 * Benefits linked to CSR partnerships include: employee attraction; staff retention and increased morale; customer loyalty; brand enhancement and differentiation; and new market opportunities.\par \par \uc2 To conclude our work with J&J, our group of four will present our recommendations on the business case for CSR to J&J\u8217\'20\'19s US-based executive committee via webinar.\par \par \uc2 As we continue to pave our career paths, it is important we understand CSR policies and the significance of corporate governance in shaping the values and practices of an organisation and its leadership. Working with J&J has given us a practical insight into applied ethics and how the wider corporate philanthropic \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  is evolving.\par \par \uc2 \u160\'00\'A0\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | gcha : \uc2 Charities/Philanthropy | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gcom : \uc2 Society/Community | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpex : \uc2 C&E Executive News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PUB\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 The Financial Times Limited (AAIW/EIW)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin